  "shareUrn": "urn:li:share:7353006436190162947",
  "text": "😅 I used to freeze and cry when speaking in front of a class. This weekend, I spoke at a tech event — twice.\n\nAt the Unconference, I spoke publicly not once but twice — first on a panel (no prep at all — just structured questions), then again in the lightning talks at the end.\nThe catch? I threw my thoughts together in 15 minutes. During a lunch break. Then had just 5 minutes to make a point.\n\nIt wasn’t polished. It wasn’t perfect. But I did it. ✨\nA few people even said they admired the courage — which made me smile, because I didn’t even hesitate. No panic. No freeze.\n\nI even kind of enjoyed it. 🎙️\n(Still can't do 1:1 conversations though. Too much social dancing. 🕺)\n\nAnd this is coming from someone who, in elementary school, couldn’t say anything in front of a class without freezing and crying. 😭\n\nConfidence isn’t something you find. It’s something you grow.\nYou don’t need to be flawless — just willing to show up, even if you’re shaky. Again and again, until one day… it’s not so scary.\n\n#BeginnersDayUnconference #EuroPython2025",
